# first-value is bring-your-own-key by default.
#
# The visitor pastes their Anthropic API key into the UI, and it is stored only
# in their browser's localStorage. Nothing is committed and nothing is sent to a
# server we run. The app calls https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages directly.
#
# There is nothing to fill in here to run the app that way.
# Just: npm install && npm run dev
#
# ---
#
# Keyless demo (optional). To run a deployed URL that does not ask each visitor
# for a key, deploy the proxy in proxy/ (it holds one key server-side) and build
# the app pointed at it. This is a build-time value, so it belongs in the build
# environment, not in client source:
#
# VITE_PROXY_URL=https://your-proxy-url
#
# The real key lives in the PROXY's own server-side environment, never in client
# code and never committed. See proxy/README.md.
#
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=      # set this in the proxy environment only
#
# ---
#
# Command-line tools (capture and eval). The scripts that produce committed
# reference runs and the live critic capability battery read the key from the
# environment: npm run capture, npm run capture:pipeline, npm run test:critic.
# To use them, copy this file to .env and set the key below. .env is gitignored,
# so it never reaches GitHub, and the tools never print it or write it to any
# output file. The npm scripts load .env automatically when it exists, so you do
# not need to export anything by hand.
#
# This is separate from the app: the browser app never reads this value. It is
# only for running the tools locally with your own key.
#
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-your-key-here   # in .env only, for the CLI tools
